red snapper fillets
cream
2 lrg pablano peppers
mexican cream
butter
flour
salt
pepper
nutmeg
Rojo
Sharp cheese (for au gratin topping)

puree 2 large poblano (large chunks) with cream. make roughx with equal butter and flower. Add pablano mix to the dark roughx. Cook over low heat, combine w/ creme fraiche (or mexican cream), salt, pepper, nutmeg.

Marinade fish with Rojo, for an hour. Pour cream mixture over fish so it is covered. Cover with cheese and bake for 20 minutes uncovered at 375. Hit in the salamander if needing to crisp the top further.
